RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 31000. FOR MN-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HARLOW'S HARMONY led the field up the backstretch, dueled while saving ground around the turn and dug in the lane, holding clear to the finish. MISSMOLLYORBIT chased the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the two path coming around the turn and dueled to the wire but could not get by the winner. STRABELLA raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening stages, began a mild bid while racing in the three path around the turn and chased the top two home in the stretch. I'M SO FUNNY raced in the middle of the pack between horses up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the turn and finished evenly. MIDNIGHT LANE was pinched back leaving the gate, trailed the field through the early going, navigated the turn from the four path and never threatend. SUMMER FIREFLYS raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend and faded in the stretch. THE MARGINS FOR THIS RACE WERE ESTIMATED BY EQUIBASE.

SHUT UP MICHAEL (IRE) dueled on the inside up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend, kicked clear in upper stretch and was caught in the final strides. OUR VALLEY chased the leader through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the turn and kept on to the finish. RIDING THE TRAIN raced in the middle of the pack on the outside early, navigated the turn from the three path and gained ground mildly in the stretch. MATTS FIRE N ICE dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battel from the two path around the bend and weakened in the final furlong. BLACKTECA raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening stages, saved ground around the turn and faded in the lane. SMOOTH SCAT raced off the pace up the backstretch, raced into tight quarters and took up headed into the turn, swung into the stretch in the four path and was empty from there. THE FINISH MARGINS FOR THIS RACE WERE ESTIMATED BY EQUIBASE.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAGECOACH BOYS raced in the three path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the outside for the run up the backstretch, dueled from the three path around the far bend and kicked clear in the stretch. CAVE HILL raced at the back of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, saved ground around the second turn, began a bid in upper stretch and gained ground late. OVERLY LUCKY raced in the three path around the first bend, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the four path coming around the far turn and kept on in the lane. BOB'S ALL IN raced off the pace on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the three path and improved position between horses in the stretch. DEVOTED TO YOU saved ground around the first turn, led the way up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the second bend and weakened late. KINETIC SWAGGER chased the leader from the two path through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the two path and faded in the lane . JOKER MATT saved ground around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and made no bid. BANDIT POINT trailed the field throughout, saved ground and was never a factor. FINAL TIME FOR THIS RACE WAS 1:38.44

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CANTERBURY PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 81. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. LILA'S LUCKY LADY led the field from the two path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to show the way while saving ground around the far bend, dueled in upper stretch and was caught near the eighth pole. CHASING SHADOWS stalked the leader on the outside through the opening half mile, began a bid from the three path coming around the second turn and chased the top two home in the lane. COME ON SWEET PEA raced in the two path around the first bend, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far turn still in the two path and made up some ground in the stretch while never threatening. MERLIN'S SISTER saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back to trail the field from the rail coming around the second bend and was not a factor from there.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHICA BOOM raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the far turn and kicked clear in the lane. ROLLIN BLACKOUT dueled from the three path around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the second bend, was caught in upper stretch and chased the winner to the wire from there. DESERT GLOW saved ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path coming around the far turn, was caught in upper stretch and kept on to the wire. LOOKIN SO LUCKY raced in the two path early, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far bend from the three path and improved position mildly in the lane. BADGER KITTEN raced in the middle of the pack on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the far turn and made up some ground in the stretch while never truly threatening. FAT AND FURIOUS raced at the back of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, continued around the far turn still in the two path and passed tiring horses in the stretch. MORE ROMANCE raced in the three path early, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the second turn in the four path and showed no kick. RIGHT OF REFUSAL raced in the four path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, dropped back while racing in the two path around the far bend and tired further in the lane. MARINA'S GOLD trailed the field the entire way around the oval, saved ground throughout and was not a factor.
